page.content: The Wirral Peninsula can be found in the Northwest of England.The Bromborough-Eastham coastline is found on the South-East of the Wirral Peninsula.Along this shore are lots of features like the ones below. JOB'S FERRY. Jobs ferry may have been around in the 1500 hundreds.It was about 300 yards north of the present jetty. LEVERHULME FIELD'S.Leverhulme fields were built by W.H.Lever for{ {recreation.}The fields were only for the workers in Sunlight Soap. CARLETT PARK. Is a large {education} college and has a variety of foreign students.
